the illegal immigration problem was started by continued and made worse by government 100 years ago we had free and open borders to the south and supply and demand for labor determined how many came
<|end_header_id|>If supply and demand determined the number of immigrants, then why don't we see the same thing happening today? In other words, if the demand for labor is so high, why aren't more immigrants coming? The truth is that the immigration system is a mess, but it is a mess that can be solved by changing a few things, instead of pretending that everything is fine just because things were that way a long time ago.
